field.value:
The ViewAtDesignTime implementation of Properties is a generic Dictionary. The AspViewBase implementation is an IDictionary. So, if I want to do Properties.ContainsKey("Foo") VS likes it, but vCompile complains that IDictionary does not contain that method, so you need to use Properties.Contains, which make VS unhappy. I suggest settling the matter by adding a simple, stolen from brail, IsDefined method to AspViewBase:

/// <summary>
        /// Determines whether the specified key is defined in the Properties collection.
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="key">The key.</param>
        /// <returns>
        /// 	<c>true</c> if the specified key is defined; otherwise, <c>false</c>.
        /// </returns>
        protected bool IsDefined(string key)
        {
            return properties.Contains(key);
        }
